The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Life

 Style of spring

 Models Sheena and Jessica 

 sport pieces from the spring line of jewellery from 

 Diagold. Picture by Rashbehari Das

What: 

 An exhibition showcasing the spring collection of jewellery 

 from Diagold.

 Where: The showroom at 4, Lee Road, Sumangal Apartment.

 When: March 21 and 22, between 11 am and 8 pm.

 Take a look: The spring line from Diagold boasts jewellery from Mumbai in a blend of Indian and western styles.

 The collection comprises cascading pendants, pendant sets, chandelier earrings and bracelets. The pieces are made of gold or white metal studded with diamonds and coloured stones, both precious and semi-precious. 

 so on offer are unconventional pieces like chokers and stone-studded gold mesh.

 The highlight of the line is the wide variety of coloured stones cut to precision to create a range of regular and occasion-wear jewellery. 

 From cappuccino, champagne, cognac browns to peachy pinks, emerald greens, golden topazes, aqua blues and tourmalines, the collection boasts all the soft and elegant colours of the season. 

 Voiceover: The collection reflects the colours and cheer of spring. It is also in sync with trends of the season and is very wearable. The pieces are stylish, chic and very trendy, says Varda Goenka of Diagold.




